---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Motherlabs — The lab behind Ada"
  description="Motherlabs is a one-person AI lab building the semantic layer between human intent and governed execution. Ada is what came out of it."
>
  <Nav />

  <main>

    <!-- ─── HERO ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="eyebrow">Motherlabs</p>
        <h1>A lab built around<br />one conviction.</h1>
        <p class="hero-sub">
          The gap between what you mean and what gets built is not a prompting problem.
          It is a structural one. And it is solvable.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── ORIGIN ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container container--split">
        <div class="split-label">
          <span class="label-text">Origin</span>
        </div>
        <div class="split-body">
          <p>
            Motherlabs is one person and a specific problem. Not a team, not a brand —
            a lab in the original sense. A place where you run experiments until something
            true comes out the other end.
          </p>
          <p>
            It started in late 2024. I was building with Claude Code and kept running into
            the same wall: the AI built what it inferred I meant, not what I actually meant.
            The inference was close. Close enough to ship. Wrong enough to undo.
          </p>
          <p>
            ~400 iterations later, I understood the problem precisely enough to solve it.
            Intent was never formalized before building started. Every session was a fresh
            guess. The drift was structural. So the fix had to be structural.
          </p>
          <blockquote>
            <p>I built Ada because I needed it. That is not a marketing line.
            It means the product was tested against a real problem before it was
            tested against a market.</p>
          </blockquote>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── BELIEFS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section section--surface section--sym">
      <span class="sym-watermark sym-watermark--right" aria-hidden="true">◆</span>
      <div class="container">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">What we believe</p>
        <div class="beliefs">
          <div class="belief">
            <span class="belief-num">01</span>
            <div class="belief-body">
              <h3>Intent should be formal before building starts.</h3>
              <p>
                Informal requirements are ambiguous by construction. Every AI model that
                builds from a chat description is building from a guess. Formalizing intent
                first is not overhead — it is the difference between governed execution
                and expensive iteration.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="belief">
            <span class="belief-num">02</span>
            <div class="belief-body">
              <h3>Capability without governance produces drift.</h3>
              <p>
                The most capable AI coding tools still produce code that drifts from
                what you meant, session by session, inference by inference. Capability
                is necessary. Governance — structure that makes the right thing the
                only thing that can be built — is what makes it reliable.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="belief">
            <span class="belief-num">03</span>
            <div class="belief-body">
              <h3>The right architecture prevents more drift than the best prompts.</h3>
              <p>
                You cannot prompt your way out of a structural problem. A hook that
                enforces a constraint at every tool boundary is worth more than a
                paragraph in CLAUDE.md. Architecture is enforcement. Prompts are advice.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="belief">
            <span class="belief-num">04</span>
            <div class="belief-body">
              <h3>One person can build a reliable system if they iterate long enough.</h3>
              <p>
                Solo does not mean limited. It means accountable. Every decision traces
                back to one understanding of the problem. There are no handoffs where
                intent gets lost. The product reflects exactly what was understood,
                for better or worse, until it is right.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── ADA ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container container--split">
        <div class="split-label">
          <span class="label-text">The product</span>
        </div>
        <div class="split-body">
          <h2>Ada</h2>
          <p>
            Ada came out of this lab. It runs before Claude Code starts. You describe what you
            want to build — at whatever level you think in. Ada identifies blocking unknowns,
            asks the minimum set of questions to resolve them, then compiles your intent into
            CLAUDE.md, agent files, and hook files that Claude Code reads every session.
          </p>

          <div class="ada-tui">
            <div class="tui-bar">
              <span class="tui-dot"></span>
              <span class="tui-dot"></span>
              <span class="tui-dot"></span>
              <span class="tui-title">ada compile</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tui-body">
              <div class="tui-prompt">
                <span class="tui-ps1">$</span>
                <span class="tui-cmd">ada compile</span>
                <span class="tui-cursor" aria-hidden="true">▋</span>
              </div>
              <div class="tui-stages">
                <div class="tui-stage"><span class="tui-glyph done">◆</span><span class="tui-code">CTX</span><span class="tui-desc">codebase context</span></div>
                <div class="tui-stage"><span class="tui-glyph done">◆</span><span class="tui-code">INT</span><span class="tui-desc">intent graph</span></div>
                <div class="tui-stage"><span class="tui-glyph done">◆</span><span class="tui-code">PER</span><span class="tui-desc">persona mapping</span></div>
                <div class="tui-stage"><span class="tui-glyph done">◆</span><span class="tui-code">ENT</span><span class="tui-desc">entity extraction</span></div>
                <div class="tui-stage"><span class="tui-glyph done">◆</span><span class="tui-code">PRO</span><span class="tui-desc">process synthesis</span></div>
                <div class="tui-stage"><span class="tui-glyph done">◆</span><span class="tui-code">SYN</span><span class="tui-desc">synthesis</span></div>
                <div class="tui-stage"><span class="tui-glyph gov">◈</span><span class="tui-code">GOV</span><span class="tui-desc tui-approved">approved &nbsp;0.94</span></div>
              </div>
              <div class="tui-output">
                <div class="tui-out-row"><span class="tui-out-file">CLAUDE.md</span><span class="tui-out-action">written</span></div>
                <div class="tui-out-row"><span class="tui-out-file">agents/</span><span class="tui-out-action">8 files written</span></div>
                <div class="tui-out-row"><span class="tui-out-file">hooks/</span><span class="tui-out-action">pre-tool guards written</span></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="ada-links">
            <a href="/ada" class="ada-link-primary">What Ada does &rarr;</a>
            <a href="/start" class="ada-link-secondary">Get started</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── HORIZON ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section section--surface">
      <div class="container container--split">
        <div class="split-label">
          <span class="label-text">What's next</span>
        </div>
        <div class="split-body">
          <p>
            The compilation pipeline is live. Elicitation is live. The world model —
            persistent artifacts that make Ada's compiled understanding navigable and
            queryable across sessions — is the current build.
          </p>
          <p>
            The goal has not changed: from first idea to last commit, Ada is the semantic
            authority for the software. Every decision traces back to the original intent.
            Drift is detectable. The right thing is structurally the only thing that can be built.
          </p>
          <p>
            Ada's relationship to Motherlabs is what Claude Code is to Anthropic —
            the execution layer that proves the thesis of the lab.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── CONTACT ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section section--contact">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="contact-inner">
          <p class="contact-sub">One person. Questions welcome.</p>
          <a href="https://github.com/alexrozex/ada" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="contact-link">
            GitHub &rarr;
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .container { max-width: 72rem; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 4rem); }
  .container--split { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 10rem 1fr; gap: 4rem; align-items: start; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .container--split { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; } }

  /* ── Hero ── */
  .hero { padding: 8rem 0 7rem; }
  .eyebrow { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-accent); margin: 0 0 2rem; }
  .hero h1 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem); font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1.08; margin: 0 0 1.75rem; color: var(--color-text); max-width: 22rem; }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 1.125rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); max-width: 36rem; margin: 0; line-height: 1.75; }

  /* ── Sections ── */
  .section { padding: 6rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .section--surface { background-color: var(--color-surface); }
  .section-eyebrow { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-text-dim); margin: 0 0 3rem; }

  /* ── Split layout ── */
  .split-label { padding-top: 0.35rem; }
  .label-text { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-text-dim); }
  .split-body { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }
  .split-body p { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin: 0; line-height: 1.85; }
  .split-body h2 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.25rem); font-weight: 400; color: var(--color-text); margin: 0; }

  blockquote { border-left: 2px solid var(--color-accent); padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem; margin: 0; background-color: var(--color-surface); }
  blockquote p { font-size: 1rem !important; color: var(--color-text) !important; font-style: italic; line-height: 1.7 !important; }

  /* ── Beliefs ── */
  .beliefs { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .beliefs { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .belief { padding: 2.5rem 2rem 2.5rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; align-items: flex-start; }
  .belief:nth-child(even) { padding-left: 2rem; border-left: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .belief:nth-child(even) { padding-left: 0; border-left: none; } }
  .belief-num { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.65rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-accent); padding-top: 0.3rem; flex-shrink: 0; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
  .belief-body { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; }
  .belief-body h3 { font-size: 0.9375rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text); margin: 0; line-height: 1.4; }
  .belief-body p { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin: 0; line-height: 1.75; }

  /* ── Ada TUI showcase ── */
  .ada-tui {
    background-color: #0F0E0C;
    border: 1px solid #2E2921;
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  .tui-bar {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
    background-color: #181612;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #2E2921;
  }

  .tui-dot {
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: #2E2921;
  }

  .tui-title {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: #6B5643;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-left: 0.5rem;
  }

  .tui-body { padding: 1.5rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; }

  .tui-prompt { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .tui-ps1 { color: #6B5643; font-size: 0.875rem; }
  .tui-cmd { color: #F0E9DF; font-size: 0.875rem; }
  .tui-cursor { color: #C8762C; font-size: 0.875rem; animation: cursor-blink 1.2s step-end infinite; }

  .tui-stages { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.3rem; }
  .tui-stage { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1rem 2.5rem 1fr; gap: 0.75rem; align-items: center; font-size: 0.8125rem; }
  .tui-glyph { font-size: 0.6rem; }
  .tui-glyph.done { color: #C8762C; }
  .tui-glyph.gov { color: #C8762C; animation: diamond-breathe 3s ease-in-out infinite; }
  .tui-code { color: #6B5643; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }
  .tui-desc { color: #A89278; }
  .tui-approved { color: #C8762C; }

  .tui-output { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.2rem; border-top: 1px solid #2E2921; padding-top: 1rem; }
  .tui-out-row { display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; font-size: 0.8125rem; }
  .tui-out-file { color: #F0E9DF; min-width: 8rem; }
  .tui-out-action { color: #6B5643; }

  /* ── Ada links ── */
  .ada-links { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1.5rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .ada-link-primary { font-size: 0.9375rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--color-accent); transition: color 120ms ease; }
  .ada-link-primary:hover { color: var(--color-accent-hover); }
  .ada-link-secondary { font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); transition: color 120ms ease; }
  .ada-link-secondary:hover { color: var(--color-text); }

  /* ── Symbol watermarks ── */
  .section--sym { position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
  .sym-watermark {
    position: absolute;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: clamp(14rem, 28vw, 22rem);
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--color-text);
    opacity: 0.028;
    user-select: none;
    pointer-events: none;
    top: 50%;
    left: -3rem;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
  }
  .sym-watermark--right { left: auto; right: -3rem; }

  /* ── Contact ── */
  .section--contact { border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .contact-inner { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1.5rem; }
  .contact-sub { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin: 0; }
  .contact-link { font-size: 0.9375rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--color-accent); transition: color 120ms ease; }
  .contact-link:hover { color: var(--color-accent-hover); }
</style>
